Design a PHP program that simulates a ticket booking queue using built-in array functions.

A ticket booking queue can be simulated in PHP using array functions like:
array_push() → add a customer to the end of the queue
array_shift() → remove (serve) the customer from the front of the queue
That’s exactly how a queue works (FIFO – First In, First Out).

CODE:
<?php
// Initialize an empty queue
$queue = array();

// Function to add customer to the queue
function addCustomer(&$queue, $name) {
    array_push($queue, $name); // add to the end
    echo "$name has joined the booking queue.<br>";
}

// Function to serve customer (remove from queue)
function serveCustomer(&$queue) {
    if (!empty($queue)) {
        $served = array_shift($queue); // remove from the front
        echo "$served's ticket has been booked!<br>";
    } else {
        echo "No customers in the queue.<br>";
    }
}

// Function to display the queue
function showQueue($queue) {
    if (!empty($queue)) {
        echo "Current Queue: " . implode(" → ", $queue) . "<br><br>";
    } else {
        echo "Queue is empty.<br><br>";
    }
}

// Simulation
addCustomer($queue, "Alice");
addCustomer($queue, "Bob");
addCustomer($queue, "Charlie");

showQueue($queue);

serveCustomer($queue);
showQueue($queue);

serveCustomer($queue);
showQueue($queue);

serveCustomer($queue);
showQueue($queue);

serveCustomer($queue); // testing when empty
?>

OUTPUT:
Alice has joined the booking queue.
Bob has joined the booking queue.
Charlie has joined the booking queue.
Current Queue: Alice → Bob → Charlie

Alice's ticket has been booked!
Current Queue: Bob → Charlie

Bob's ticket has been booked!
Current Queue: Charlie
Charlie's ticket has been booked!
Queue is empty.

No customers in the queue.
